Upstream TF-A v2.14.x for RK3399 links BL31 .pmusram into PMUSRAM_RSIZE (8 KiB).
With current M0 blobs + AArch64 glue, GNU ld overflows by ~3.9 KiB on Ubuntu
aarch64-linux-gnu-11. Expand the reserved BL31 PMU SRAM budget to 16 KiB; total
PMU SRAM window remains SIZE_K(64).

Apply from TF-A tree root: patch -p1 < path/to/this/file

--- a/plat/rockchip/rk3399/include/shared/addressmap_shared.h
+++ b/plat/rockchip/rk3399/include/shared/addressmap_shared.h
@@ -64,7 +64,7 @@
 #define PMUGRF_SIZE		SIZE_K(64)
 #define SGRF_SIZE		SIZE_K(64)
 #define PMUSRAM_SIZE		SIZE_K(64)
-#define PMUSRAM_RSIZE		SIZE_K(8)
+#define PMUSRAM_RSIZE		SIZE_K(16)
 #define PWM_SIZE		SIZE_K(64)
 #define CIC_SIZE		SIZE_K(4)
 #define DCF_SIZE		SIZE_K(4)
